§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ A ❬monoid❭ is an algebra $(S, ·)$ for which (1) $·$ is
    associative and (2) $S$ has a unit element under $·$. ⦉

  ‖ If the operation is commutative, then we call the monoid ❬
    commutative❭ (or ❬abelian❭). ⦉
